Constructor Detail

LinkedLevels

public LinkedLevels()
default constructor. makes the root StringLevel and names it, setting it as the current StringLevel.

Method Detail

in

public void in()
goes "in" a level, creating a new level that is an offshoot of the current one. this new level will have a depth that is +1 of the current depth. this new level will be a "child" of the current level.

getDepth

public int getDepth()
returns the depth of the curent StringLevel.

Returns:
the current StringLevel's depth.

out

public void out()
goes "out" a level. if this is the root object, an exception is thrown. otherwise, sets the current StringLevel to the "parent" StringLevel of the current StringLevel.

Throws:
java.lang.IllegalStateException - - when the current StringLevel is the root.

toString

public java.lang.String toString()

root

private LinkedLevels.Level root()
returns the root Level of this LinkedLevels object. Done by following links back from current level. Does not change the pointer for the current level.

Returns:
the root level.

returnToTop

private LinkedLevels.Level returnToTop()
returns the root Level of this LinkedLevels object. Done by following links back from current level. WARNING: changes the current pointer to the root level.

Returns:
the root level.
